  "bio": [
    "👋 Hi! I'm <strong>Nahid Ahmadvand</strong>, focused on <strong class=\"text-green-400\">data science</strong> and <strong class=\"text-purple-400\">machine learning</strong>, with a strong academic background in physics, quantum information, and mathematical modeling.",
    "🎓 I earned my M.Sc. in Quantum Information and Computation from Sharif University of Technology and my B.Sc. in Physics from the University of Tehran, where I graduated ranked 1st by GPA in the B.Sc. Physics program.",
    "🤖 I build hands-on machine learning projects focused on practical data science workflows, reliable model evaluation, and clear communication, with interests in NLP, predictive modeling, and Formula 1 data analytics.",
    "📊 My work emphasizes practical machine learning habits: leakage-aware validation, interpretable baselines, careful feature engineering, error analysis, explainability, and clear communication of results.",
    "✍️ I write technical articles on Medium to document my projects, explain modeling decisions, and share what actually improves performance beyond simply using more complex algorithms.",
    "🔬 Before moving toward data science, I worked in physics education and research. My master's thesis research was published in Physical Review A, and my teaching experience strengthened my ability to explain complex technical ideas clearly."
  ],
